The research that led to the scientific knowledge on the dynamics and causes of Gulf of Mexico hypoxia was funded by the following agencies, grants, and initiatives: the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) National Ocean Service, the NOAA Nutrient Enhanced Coastal Ocean Productivity program, the NOAA Coastal Ocean Program, the NOAA National Undersea Research Program, the NOAA Northern Gulf of Mexico Program, the Louisiana Sea Grant College Program, the Minerals Management Service (MMS) University Research Initiative, MMS's Louisiana–Texas Physical Oceanography Program, the US Department of Energy's National Institute for Global Environmental Change, the Louisiana Board of Regents Support Fund, the Gulf of Mexico Program, and the Louisiana Universities Marine Consortium under the leadership of Donald F. Boesch. We thank Donald E. Pryor for his insightful comments on early drafts of this manuscript. The task force and integrated assessment benefited from the collaboration of many individuals under the leadership and guidance of Chuck Fox and Rosina Bierbaum, respectively. We continue to thank Ben Cole for his assistance with graphics and data management and retrieval.
