Author notes
1
Nancy N. Rabalais ( nrabalais@lumcon.edu ) is a professor at the Louisiana Universities Marine Consortium, Chauvin, Louisiana 70344.
2
R. Eugene Turner is a professor in the Department of Oceanography and Coastal Sciences, Louisiana State University, Baton Rouge, LA 70803.
3
Rabalais and Turner have been collaborating on hypoxia research since 1985.
4
Donald Scavia is the chief scientist of the National Ocean Service of the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) and director of the National Centers for Coastal Ocean Science at NOAA, Silver Spring, MD 20910. He chaired the Integrated Assessment team and served as the US Department of Commerce alternate on the Mississippi River/Gulf of Mexico Watershed Nutrient Task Force.
Editor's note: This article was derived from a plenary address at the March 2001 AIBS annual meeting.
